Subject:[CT Birds] Updated State Parks list
Hammo is still closed as of today.

Parks and Forest Areas that are open to the public, as of November 1, 2012:

Black Rock State Park, Watertown
Dinosaur State Park, Rocky Hill
Fort Griswold State Park
Fort Trumbull State Park, New London
Haddam Meadows State Park, Haddam
Harkness Memorial State Park, Waterford
Gillette Castle State Park, East Haddam (grounds open, Castle and
Visitor Center closed)
Kellogg Environmental Center, Derby
Mashamoquet State Park, Pomfret
Millers Pond State Park, Haddam/Durham
Nachaug State Forest, Eastford
Pachaug State Forest, Voluntown
Putnam Memorial State Park, Redding
Quaddick State Park, Thompson
Topsmead State Forest, Litchfield
Wadsworth Falls State Park, Middletown/Middlefield

Here's the website with this list:
http://www.ct.gov/dep/cwp/view.asp?a=2716&q=325086&depNav_GID=1650

